title: Florida State Road 53
text:
State Road 53 (SR 53) is a north–south <a href="State%20highway%20%28US%29">state highway</a> in the <a href="Florida%20Panhandle">panhandle</a> of northern <a href="Florida">Florida</a>. Its southern terminus is an <a href="Interchange%20%28road%29">interchange</a> with <a href="Interstate%2010%20in%20Florida">Interstate 10</a> (I-10; which also carries the <a href="Unsigned%20highway">unsigned</a> designation of <a href="Florida%20State%20Road%208">SR 8</a>) near <a href="Lee%2C%20Florida">Lee</a> and <a href="Madison%2C%20Florida">Madison</a>; the northern terminus is at the <a href="Georgia%20%28U.S.%20state%29">Georgia</a> state line near <a href="Cherry%20Lake%2C%20Florida">Cherry Lake, Florida</a>. Part of SR 53, from Harvey Greene Drive north to <a href="Florida%20State%20Road%2014">SR 14</a>, is also signed <a href="Florida%20State%20Road%2014%20Truck">SR 14 Truck</a>, a rare <a href="special%20route">special</a> state highway in Florida.
SR 53 continues northward from the state line as <a href="Georgia%20State%20Route%20333">State Route 333</a> (SR 333). A southbound continuation of SR 53 is County Road 53, which ultimately ends at an <a href="Intersection%20%28road%29">intersection</a> with <a href="U.S.%20Route%2027%20in%20Florida">U.S. Route 27</a> (US 27; which also carries the unsigned designation of <a href="Florida%20State%20Road%2020">SR 20</a>) in <a href="Buckville%2C%20Florida">Buckville</a> (northwest of <a href="Mayo%2C%20Florida">Mayo</a>). This is also the western terminus of <a href="County%20Road%20534%20%28Lafayette%20County%2C%20Florida%29">CR 534</a>.
